cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.HC, cs.IR 

The paper discusses the methods and implications of web tracking, which falls under the category of computer security and privacy. Therefore, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the user's defenses against tracking, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also mentions the use of web caches and fingerprinting, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
